  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/ontology/gist/exponentOfKilogram",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "DEFINITION: The exponent of kilogram in a product of powers of base units."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "EXAMPLE: In the equation '1 millimole per gram = 1 x mole per kilogram'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversion factor for millimole per gram is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of mole is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of kilogram is -1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing millimole per gram must be a multiple of mole per kilogram."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain": [
      {
        "@id": "_:b16861dd9e2d7869a"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore14.1.0"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "exponent of kilogram"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "The exponent of kilogram in a product of powers of base units."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "In the equation '1 millimole per gram = 1 x mole per kilogram'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversion factor for millimole per gram is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of mole is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of kilogram is -1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing millimole per gram must be a multiple of mole per kilogram."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "exponent of kilogram"
